properties.headline: Gale Watch issued January 19 at 8:59PM PST until January 21 at 6:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Small Craft Advisory, south winds 15 to 25 kt
and seas 9 to 13 feet at 18 seconds. For the Gale Watch,
southeast winds 25 to 35 kt and seas 12 to 15 feet at 15
seconds possible.

* WHERE...Coastal Waters from Cape Flattery to Cape Shoalwater
out to 60 nm.

* WHEN...For the Small Craft Advisory, until 6 PM PST Monday.
For the Gale Watch, from Monday evening through late Monday
night.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds can cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
A Gale Watch is issued when the risk of gale force winds of 34 to
47 knots has significantly increased, but the specific timing
and/or location is still uncertain. It is intended to provide
additional lead time for mariners who may wish to consider
altering their plans.
